	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories A man has died after a concrete pump house collapsed and
fell on him in La Lucia, Durban, on Wednesday. Netcare 911 said it responded to reports of a structural
collapse on Lady Ellen Crescent in La Lucia. "Reports from the scene indicate that a concrete
structure collapsed on a construction worker. "The patient was assessed on scene by an advanced
life-support paramedic and found to have no signs of life," the emergency
service provider said. The man was declared dead on the scene. "The fire and rescue services as well as the SAPS
[were] on scene to help remove the man from the rubble," Netcare 911 said. KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24 on Twitter  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  